1. Evaluating a film from the perspective of history and society;
2. Watched more clips and films and learnt more about it that are screened before 1970 that may not be so focused on by me before;
3. Ways of finding both primary and secondary resources, especially magazines and newspapers.

Strengths:
1. Very informative and have a holistic view;
2. The two main topics of this course, which are film and American history, are closely related and connected;
3. Plenty of time for on-class screening, which is very helpful.

Weakness:
1. Sometimes some topics and historical period are not fully discussed because of the arrangement of the course, while some are sort of over-discussed.
